I ate a couple bites of chicken chorizo yesterday (on accident)

Probably the most meat I've eatten in 10 years and I've felt weird since, like I have no appetite 

unsure what to make of this

1) is possibly met by oysters, which might as well not be sentient (at least, probably not more sentient than plants)

2) is possibly met by liver and fatty fish. I haven't really done a lot of research here to know
might be healthy, I'm generally open to new things
Fill in the gaps type tweet

Full quote 

Those who follow the rituals given in the Vedas, who offer sacrifices and take soma, free themselves from evil and attain the vast heaven of the gods, where they enjoy celestial pleasures. (1/2)
When they have enjoyed these fully, their merit is exhausted and they return to this land of death. Thus observing Vedic rituals but caught in an endless chain of desires, they come and go. (2/2)
